{"title":"Olympic BMX hopeful Twan van Gendt’s bike adds derailleur to shift gears to BMX Gold?","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/22/olympic-bmx-hopeful-twan-van-gendts-bike-adds-derailleur-to-shift-gears-to-gold/","date":1626969969000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>BMX World Champion is on his way to Tokyo 2020 right now with a prototype 2-speed BMX bike that is sure to shake up the Olympics, if not just the conversation. A carbon, geared hardtail with a Zee DH rear derailleur, a chain guide, and flat mount XTR disc brakes, yeah that’s not what usually comes to mind when I think BMX racing. But I’m certainly not one to judge the World Champion, and cyclist Twan van Gendt surely knows what he’s doing, having refined his Olympic start in his backyard in The Netherlands for the last nine months on a Tokyo-replica start ramp…</p><h2>OMG 2-speed geared Meybo Olympic BMX bike of Twan van Gendt</h2><figure id=\"attachment_266264\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-266264\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115758/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115758/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb26/ng:webp/ngcb26\" alt=\"Olympic BMX prototype 2-speed derailleur gears Meybo bike, BMX World Champion Twan van Gendt\" width=\"1350\" height=\"900\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115758/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 1350w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115758/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-deraille