-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_Zee-shifter-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22120137/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_Zee-shifter-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22120137/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_Zee-shifter-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a></p><p>We’re not 100% sure on his individual gearing choice, but it looks like a combination of 14T &amp; 16T cogs out back. Up front is a single narrow-wide 48T chainring on a Shimano DXR BMX crankset, with an XLC CR-A18 chainguide mounted backward off the tiny BMX seattube to keep the chain aligned behind that massive ring.</p><figure id=\"attachment_266259\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-266259\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice.jpg\" alt=\"Olympic BMX prototype 2-speed derailleur gears Meybo bike, BMX World Champion Twan van Gendt, training\" width=\"1350\" height=\"675\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice.jpg 1350w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice-297x149.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice-800x400.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice-120x60.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice-768x384.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice-696x348.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice-1068x534.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice-840x420.jpg 840w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1350px) 100vw, 1350px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice.jpg 1350w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice-297x149.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice-800x400.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice-120x60.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice-768x384.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice-696x348.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice-1068x534.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22115728/Olympic-BMX-prototype-2-speed-derailleur-gears-Meybo-bike_BMX-World-Champion-Twan-van-Gendt_practice-840x420.jpg 840w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-266259\">all photos c. Twan van Gendt</figcaption></figure><p>The new 2022 Meybo HSX Carbon frame itself features standards we’ll recognize from MTB, like a 1.5″ tapered internal headset, a wide BB368 EVO bottom bracket, flat mount rear disc brake mounting, what appears to be a 15mm rear thru-axle, and a replaceable derailleur hanger. Conventional singlespeed BMX drivetrains use an integrated Meybo chain tensioner, which obviously van Gendt has replaced with a derailleur. It includes internal routing for the rear brake line, but not for the unconventional derailleur cable.</p><p>The only question remaining, is whether the unique 2-speed BMX drivetrain will give Twan van Gendt the edge he needs to repeat his World Championship win on the Tokyo 2020 Olympic BMX track.</p><p><a href=\"https://meybobikes.com/2022/232-meybo-hsx-carbon-bmx-race-frame-blackudgrey.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>MeyboBikes.com</em></a></p><h3>Olympic BMX Competition: How To Watch</h3><p><span><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/T51G1LdTQiE?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></p><p>Tune in to the Ariake Urban Sports Park racing action which kicks off with Quarterfinals on July 29th, then Semifinal &amp; Finals on the 30th.</p><p>Check out our <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/19/olympic-bmx-racing-and-bmx-freestyle-how-to-watch-bmx-at-the-olympics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">full Olympic BMX feature</a> to learn more about the racing (and new BMX Freestyle) and to stay up-to-date on how &amp; when to watch Olympic BMX.</p></div></div>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"949c84ee985ef0b8de95b3cd0dae8b12f66111c2f91becc66bd4c901b23040ac","category":"Cycling"}